### Ingredients 

## for the filling 

6 big apples (Belle de Boskoo)
4 tea spoons sugar 
1 table spoon flour 
1 tea spoon lemon juice
10 gr butter (for oiling the pan)
1 table spoon vanila sugar

## for the crumble 

100 gr flour
80 gr oats
40 gr almonds powder 
1 table spoon vanila sugar
150 gr light Brown Sugar
170 gr salted Butter (Cut into cubes)

### Instructions

## Filling 

Pre heat the oven to 200 C

Oil the pan with the butter 
Cut the apples into the pan
Spread the lemon juice on the apples 
Spread all the dry ingredients on the apples and mix everything in
the pan. 
Press the apple mixture into an even layer.
bake for 15 minutes.


## Crumble

Mix all crumble ingredients until the butter is fully immersed and you have chunks of dough.
Take the apples out of the oven
Spread the chunks on the apples
Put the pan back in the oven
reduce the heat to 180 and bake for 30-40 minutes

